# AI-OS — sensitive .ai/ files should not be committed
# Rename this to .gitignore inside .ai/ (done by ai init)

# Contains env var names and secret storage details
ENV.md

# Contains architecture decisions that may reveal security posture
# Comment out if you want to track decisions in git
# DECISIONS.md

# Contains AI session logs (may include sensitive context)
SESSION.md
LOG.md

# Contains questions/answers that may include sensitive business logic
# Comment out if you want to track Q&A in git
# QUESTIONS.md

# Contains cross-agent messages (may include sensitive context)
COMM.md

# Archive directory
archive/

# SQLite runtime database — binary artifact, regenerated by task-synchronizer-mcp
state.sqlite
state.sqlite-shm
state.sqlite-wal

# DIGEST.md is committed by default — it's the primary AI cache and usually safe.
# If your DIGEST contains sensitive architecture details, uncomment:
# DIGEST.md
